name: Team Rocket's Pupitar

attacks.name: Explosive Ascension
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

name: Nosepass
flavorText: The magnet in Nosepass's nose provides an unerring compass, making this Pokémon an excellent partner for Trainers going on a journey.

name: Medicham

attacks.name: Harmonious Spirit Palm
attacks.text: If this Pokémon and your opponent's Active Pokémon have the same amount of Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

flavorText: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.

name: Regirock ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Regi Charge
attacks.text: Attach up to 2 Basic Fighting Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Giant Rock
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Stage 2 Pokémon, this attack does 140 more damage.

name: Mudsdale

abilities.name: Mud Coat
abilities.text: This Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: This Pokémon has been treasured not just for its physical labor but also because it produces high-quality mud used for making pottery.

name: Team Rocket's Koffing

abilities.name: Smog Signals
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), search your deck for up to 2 Pokémon that have "Koffing" in their name and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.

name: Marnie's Liepard

attacks.name: Pointy Claws
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 70 more damage.

flavorText: This stealthy Pokémon sneaks up behind prey without making any sound at all. It competes with Thievul for territory.

name: Marnie's Scraggy

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It stretches its saggy skin up to its neck to protect itself. Among Scraggy, individuals with saggier skin apparently garner more respect.

name: Marnie's Scrafty

attacks.name: Wild Tackle
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

name: Marnie's Impidimp

attacks.name: Filch
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: The reason this Pokémon causes trouble for those it feels close to is because Impidimp itself gets irritable if it can't absorb negative emotions.

name: Marnie's Morgrem
flavorText: Morgrem prefers dirty tactics, like ambushing, because it doesn't have confidence in its brawn.

name: Marnie's Grimmsnarl ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Punk Up
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 5 Basic Darkness Energy cards and attach them to your Marnie's Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Shadow Bullet
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

name: Marnie's Morpeko

attacks.name: Spiky Wheel
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Darkness Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Morpeko eats seeds constantly to keep its hunger at bay. If it's hungry for too long, it grows wild and brutish.

name: Arven's Maschiff
flavorText: It always scowls in an attempt to make opponents take it seriously, but even crying children will burst into laughter when they see Maschiff's face.

name: Arven's Mabosstiff ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Vigorous Tackle
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has no damage counters on it, this attack does 120 more damage.

attacks.name: Boss Headbutt
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Boss Headbutt.

name: Forretress

attacks.name: Iron Shake-Up
attacks.text: You may move any amount of Metal Energy from your Pokémon to your other Pokémon in any way you like.

attacks.name: Hurricane of Needles
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It's usually found hanging on to a fat tree trunk. It shoots out bits of its shell when it sees action.

name: Skarmory

attacks.name: Roost
attacks.text: Heal 50 damage from this Pokémon. During your next turn, this Pokémon can't retreat.

flavorText: Its sturdy, heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.

name: Steven's Skarmory

attacks.name: Sonic Double
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Its sturdy, heavy-looking iron body is actually thin and light, so it can fly at speeds over 180 mph.

name: Steven's Beldum
flavorText: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground's natural magnetism, letting it float.

name: Steven's Metang

attacks.name: Metal Slash
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.

name: Steven's Metagross ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: X-Boot
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Basic Psychic Energy card, a Basic Metal Energy card, or 1 of each and attach them to your Psychic Pokémon and Metal Pokémon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Zamazenta

attacks.name: Strong Bash
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokémon is damaged by an attack (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon equal to the damage done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its ability to deflect any attack led to it being known as the Fighting Master's Shield. It was feared and respected by all.

name: Team Rocket's Rattata

attacks.name: Dangerous Incisors
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: This Pokémon is common but hazardous. Its sharp incisors can easily cut right through hard wood.

name: Team Rocket's Raticate

attacks.name: Reckless Abandon
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are tails, this Pokémon also does 90 damage to itself.

flavorText: Its whiskers are essential for maintaining its balance. No matter how friendly you are, it will get angry and bite you if you touch its whiskers.

name: Team Rocket's Persian ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Haughty Order
attacks.text: Reveal the top 10 cards of your opponent's deck. You may choose an attack from a Pokémon you find there and use it as this attack. Shuffle the revealed cards into your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Cruel Slash
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

name: Team Rocket's Meowth

attacks.name: Paw-cket Pilfer
attacks.text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck.

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

flavorText: All it does is sleep during the daytime. At night, it patrols its territory with its eyes aglow.

name: Tauros

attacks.name: Clean Hit
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is an Evolution Pokémon, this attack does 50 more damage.

flavorText: When it targets an enemy, it charges furiously while whipping its body with its long tails.

name: Kangaskhan

attacks.name: Dizzy Punch
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

flavorText: There are records of a lost human child being raised by a childless Kangaskhan.

name: Team Rocket's Porygon

attacks.name: Hacking
attacks.text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, your opponent discards a card from their hand.

flavorText: It is an artificial Pokémon. Since it doesn't breathe, people are excited by its potential to be useful in any environment.

name: Team Rocket's Porygon2

attacks.name: R Command
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Supporter card that has "Team Rocket" in its name in your discard pile.

flavorText: This artificial Pokémon evolved thanks to cutting- edge science. It sometimes displays behavior that is not in its programming.

name: Team Rocket's Porygon-Z

abilities.name: Reconstitute
abilities.text: You must discard 2 cards from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw a card.

attacks.name: R Command
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each Supporter card that has "Team Rocket" in its name in your discard pile.

flavorText: An additional program was installed to create a more advanced Pokémon, but it was apparently flawed. Porygon-Z moves oddly as a result.

name: Taillow
flavorText: It dislikes cold seasons. They migrate to other lands in search of warmth, flying over 180 miles a day.

name: Swellow

attacks.name: Add On
attacks.text: Draw 3 cards.

flavorText: It dives at a steep angle as soon as it spots its prey. It catches its prey with sharp claws.

name: Arven's Greedent

abilities.name: Greedy Order
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may put up to 2 Arven's Sandwich cards from your discard pile into your hand.

flavorText: If it spots a berry tree, it will immediately go to gather berries without a sideways glance—even if it's in the middle of a battle.

name: Arven's Skwovet

attacks.name: Gnaw Through
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It stores berries in its cheeks. When there are no berries to be found, Skwovet will stuff pebbles into its cheeks to stave off its cravings.

name: Squawkabilly

attacks.name: Push Down
attacks.text: You may switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

flavorText: These Pokémon prefer to live in cities. They form flocks based on the color of their feathers, and they fight over territory.

You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Cynthia's Power Weight
rules: The Cynthia's Pokémon this card is attached to gets +70 HP.
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.

name: Emcee's Hype
rules: Draw 2 cards. If your opponent has 3 or fewer Prize cards remaining, draw 2 more cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Energy Recycler
rules: Shuffle up to 5 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Ethan's Adventure
rules: Search your deck for up to 3 in any combination of Ethan's Pokémon and Basic Fire Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Granite Cave
rules: Steven's Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) take 30 less damage from attacks from the opponent's Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: Sacred Ash
rules: Shuffle up to 5 Pokémon from your discard pile into your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Spikemuth Gym
rules: Once during each player's turn, that player may search their deck for a Marnie's Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into their hand. Then, that player shuffles their deck.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: Team Rocket's Archer
rules: You can use this card only if any of your Team Rocket's Pokémon were Knocked Out during your opponent's last turn.  Each player shuffles their hand into their deck. Then, you draw 5 cards, and your opponent draws 3 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Team Rocket's Ariana
rules: Draw cards until you have 5 cards in your hand. If all of your Pokémon in play are Team Rocket's Pokémon, draw cards until you have 8 cards in your hand instead.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Team Rocket's Bother-Bot
rules: Turn 1 of your opponent's face-down Prize cards face up and choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card. You may have your opponent switch those cards. (That Prize card remains face up for the rest of the game.)
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Team Rocket's Factory
rules: Once during each player's turn, if they played a Supporter card that has "Team Rocket" in its name from their hand this turn, they may draw 2 cards.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: Team Rocket's Giovanni
rules: Switch your Active Team Rocket's Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Team Rocket's Pokémon. If you do, switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Team Rocket's Great Ball
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, search your deck for an Evolution Team Rocket's Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. If tails, search your deck for a Basic Team Rocket's Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Team Rocket's Petrel
rules: Search your deck for a Trainer card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Team Rocket's Proton
rules: If you go first, you may use this card during your first turn.  Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Team Rocket's Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Team Rocket's Transceiver
rules: Search your deck for a Supporter card that has "Team Rocket" in its name, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Team Rocket's Venture Bomb
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. If tails, put 2 damage counters on your Active Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Team Rocket's Watchtower
rules: Colorless Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: Team Rocket's Energy
rules: This card can only be attached to a Team Rocket's Pokémon. If this card is attached to anything other than a Team Rocket's Pokémon, discard this card.  As long as this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides 2 in any combination of Psychic Energy and Darkness Energy.

name: Yanma

attacks.name: Whirlwind
attacks.text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

flavorText: As Yanma surveys its territory, it periodically stops to hover in place by flapping its wings at high speeds.

name: Cynthia's Roserade

abilities.name: Cheer On to Glory
abilities.text: Attacks used by your Cynthia's Pokémon do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: The poison in its right hand is quick acting. The poison in its left hand is slow acting. Both are life threatening.

name: Shaymin

abilities.name: Flower Curtain
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to your Benched Pokémon that don't have a Rule Box by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon. (Pokémon ex, Pokémon V, etc. have Rule Boxes.)

flavorText: The blooming of Gracidea flowers confers the power of flight upon it. Feelings of gratitude are the message it delivers.

name: Crustle

abilities.name: Mysterious Rock Inn
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon ex.

attacks.name: Superb Scissors
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Its thick claws are its greatest weapons. They're mighty enough to crack Rhyperior's carapace.

name: Team Rocket's Spidops

abilities.name: Charging Up
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may attach a Basic Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Rocket Rush
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each of your Team Rocket's Pokémon in play.

flavorText: It clings to branches and ceilings using its threads and moves without a sound. It takes out its prey before the prey even notices it.

name: Hydrapple

attacks.name: Hydra Breath
attacks.text: Discard 6 Basic Grass Energy cards from your hand, and Knock Out your opponent's Active Pokémon. If you can't discard 6 cards in this way, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Seven syrpents live inside an apple made of syrup. The syrpent in the center is the commander.

name: Rapidash

abilities.name: Hurried Gait
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may draw a card.

flavorText: The fastest runner becomes the leader, and it decides the herd's pace and direction of travel.

name: Ethan's Typhlosion

attacks.name: Buddy Blast
attacks.text: This attack does 60 more damage for each Ethan's Adventure card in your discard pile.

flavorText: It has a secret, devastating move. It rubs its blazing fur to cause huge explosions.

name: Misty's Psyduck

abilities.name: Flustered Leap
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may discard the bottom card of your deck. If you do, discard all cards from this Pokémon and put this Pokémon on top of your deck.

flavorText: It is constantly wracked by a headache. When the headache turns intense, it begins using mysterious powers.

name: Team Rocket's Houndoom

attacks.name: Cruel Coal
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned and Confused.

attacks.name: Scorching Fire
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: If you are burned by the flames it shoots from its mouth, the pain will never go away.

name: Blaziken

attacks.name: Inferno Kick Flurry
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon. This attack also does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: When facing a tough foe, it looses flames from its wrists. Its powerful legs let it jump clear over buildings.

name: Misty's Lapras

attacks.name: Swim Together
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 3 Misty's Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It ferries people across the sea on its back. It may sing an enchanting cry if it is in a good mood.

name: Clamperl

attacks.name: Shell Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 10 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Clamperl's pearls are exceedingly precious. They can be more than 10 times as costly as Shellder's pearls.

name: Electrike
flavorText: It stores electricity in its fur. It gives off sparks from all over its body in seasons when the air is dry.

name: Rotom

attacks.name: Astonish
attacks.text: Choose a random card from your opponent's hand. Your opponent reveals that card and shuffles it into their deck.

attacks.name: Gadget Show
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon Tool attached to all of your Pokémon.

flavorText: Its electricity-like body can enter some kinds of machines and take control in order to make mischief.

name: Team Rocket's Orbeetle

abilities.name: Rocket Brain
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move 1 damage counter from 1 of your Team Rocket's Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Psychic
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It emits psychic energy to observe and study what's around it—and what's around it can include things over six miles away.

name: Team Rocket's Weezing

attacks.name: Explode Together Now
attacks.text: This attack does 40 damage for each Pokémon in play that has "Koffing" or "Weezing" in its name (both yours and your opponent's).

flavorText: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the highest level.

name: Team Rocket's Murkrow

attacks.name: Deceit
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Torment
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't use that attack.

flavorText: Feared and loathed by many, it is believed to bring misfortune to all those who see it at night.

abilities.text: Whenever your opponent plays an Item or Supporter card from their hand, prevent all effects of that card done to this Pokémon.

attacks.text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

attacks.text: You may do 120 more damage. If you do, this Pokémon also does 50 damage to itself.

attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.text: If this Pokémon has at least 2 extra Energy attached (in addition to this attack's cost), this attack does 100 more damage.

rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.text: This Pokémon can't attack unless you have 4 or more Team Rocket's Pokémon in play.

attacks.text: You may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

attacks.name: Draconic Buster
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Team Rocket's Nidoking ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned. During Pokémon Checkup, put 8 damage counters on that Pokémon instead of 1.

name: Team Rocket's Crobat ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Assassin's Return
attacks.text: You may put this Pokémon into your hand. (Discard all cards attached to this Pokémon.)

You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: N's Darmanitan

attacks.name: Back Draft
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Basic Energy card in your opponent's discard pile.

attacks.name: Flamebody Cannon
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon, and this attack also does 90 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: This Pokémon's power level rises along with the temperature of its fire, which can reach 2,500 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Iono's Kilowattrel

abilities.name: Flashing Draw
abilities.text: You must discard a Basic Lightning Energy from this Pokémon in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.

flavorText: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

name: Lillie's Ribombee

abilities.name: Inviting Wink
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may have your opponent reveal their hand and you put any number of Basic Pokémon you find there onto their Bench.

flavorText: Ribombee can sense when people or Pokémon are feeling down, and it will cheer them up with handmade pollen puffs.

name: Hop's Snorlax

abilities.name: Extra Helpings
abilities.text: Attacks used by your Hop's Pokémon do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance). The effect of Extra Helpings doesn't stack.

attacks.name: Dynamic Press
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 80 damage to itself.

flavorText: This gluttonous Pokémon eats constantly, apart from when it's asleep. It devours nearly 900 pounds of food per day.

name: N's Zorua
flavorText: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

name: Hop's Zacian ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Insta-Strike
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Brave Slash
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Brave Slash.

name: Iono's Bellibolt ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Electric Streamer
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn, you may attach a Basic Lightning Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Iono's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Thunderous Bolt
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

name: Lillie's Clefairy ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Fairy Zone
abilities.text: The Weakness of each of your opponent's Dragon Pokémon in play is now Psychic. (Apply Weakness as ×2.)

attacks.name: Full Moon Rondo
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Team Rocket's Wobbuffet

attacks.name: Rocket Mirror
attacks.text: Move all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Team Rocket's Pokémon to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: To keep its pitch-black tail hidden, it lives quietly in the darkness. It is never first to attack.

name: N's Sigilyph

attacks.name: Victory Symbol
attacks.text: If you use this attack when you have exactly 1 Prize card remaining, you win this game.

flavorText: A discovery was made in the desert where Sigilyph fly. The ruins of what may have been an ancient city were found beneath the sands.

name: Metagross

attacks.name: Conjoined Beams
attacks.text: If Beldum and Metang are on your Bench, this attack does 150 more damage.

flavorText: It folds its four legs when flying. Its four brains are said to be superior to a supercomputer.

name: Swinub

attacks.name: Call for Family
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It searches for food by digging into the ground with its snout. Even frozen ground doesn't give it any trouble.

name: Pupitar

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 20 damage to itself.

flavorText: This pupa flies around wildly by venting with great force the gas pressurized inside its body.

name: N's Purrloin

attacks.name: Thieving Swipe
attacks.text: Your opponent reveals their hand, and you choose a card you find there and put it on the bottom of their deck.

flavorText: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

name: N's Zoroark ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Trade
abilities.text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Night Joker
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your Benched N's Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

name: Hop's Corviknight

attacks.name: Shoot Through
attacks.text: This attack also does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Steel Wing
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 60 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Although its wings have partly turned to steel and become heavy as a result, this Pokémon flies through the skies with ease.

name: Bagon

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: Its steel-hard head can shatter boulders. It longingly hopes for wings to grow so it can fly.

name: Mamoswine ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Mammoth Hauler
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Rumbling March
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each Stage 2 Pokémon on your Bench.

name: Regirock

abilities.name: Rock Armor
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has any Energy attached, it takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Breaching Lariat
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

flavorText: Cutting-edge technology was used to study the internals of this Pokémon's rock body, but nothing was found—not even a brain or a heart.

name: Koffing
flavorText: Toxic gas is held within its thin, balloon-shaped body, so it can cause massive explosions.

name: Tyranitar

abilities.name: Daunting Gaze
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't play any Item cards from their hand.

attacks.name: Cracking Stomp
attacks.text: Discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.

flavorText: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn't care about others.

name: N's Klink

attacks.name: Double Spin
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

flavorText: The two minigears that compose this Pokémon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.

name: Salamence ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Wide Blast
attacks.text: This attack does 50 damage to each of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Dragon Impact
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon.

name: Druddigon

attacks.name: Dragon's Fury
attacks.text: Attach a Basic Fire Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Dragon Pokémon.

flavorText: Druddigon are vicious and cunning. They take up residence in nests dug out by other Pokémon, treating the stolen nests as their own lairs.

name: Sentret
flavorText: This Pokémon is extremely cautious. Its supple tail is well muscled and firm to the touch.

name: Furret
flavorText: It raises its offspring inside a long, narrow nest. Once they're old enough, it takes them outside the nest to prepare them for independence.

name: Larvitar

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Born deep underground, this Pokémon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.

name: Pancham

attacks.name: Focus Fist
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Wanting to make sure it's taken seriously, Pancham's always giving others a glare. But if it's not focusing, it ends up smiling.

name: Rockruff

attacks.name: Dig It Up
attacks.text: Look at the top card of your deck. You may discard that card.

flavorText: This Pokémon is very friendly when it's young. Its disposition becomes vicious once it matures, but it never forgets the kindness of its master.

name: Lycanroc

abilities.name: Spike-Clad
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may attach up to 2 Spiky Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Clamping Fangs
attacks.text: This attack does 40 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Lycanroc attacks its prey with its sharp claws and fangs. It loyally obeys the instructions of a Trainer it trusts.

name: Weezing

attacks.name: Pervasive Gas
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Crazy Blast
attacks.text: If this Pokémon used Pervasive Gas during your last turn, this attack does 120 more damage.

flavorText: Top-grade perfume is made using its internal poison gases by diluting them to the highest level.

name: Escavalier

attacks.name: Iron Buster
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: It charges its enemies, lances at the ready. An image of one of its duels is captured in a famous painting of Escavalier clashing with Sirfetch'd.

name: N's Klinklang

attacks.name: Triple Smash
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 120 damage for each heads.

flavorText: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.

name: Magearna

abilities.name: Auto Heal
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, whenever you attach an Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon, heal 90 damage from that Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spike Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

flavorText: Built roughly 500 years ago by a scientist, the part called the Soul-Heart is the actual life-form.

name: Shelgon

attacks.name: Guard Press
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokémon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: The cells within its shell transform with explosive speed, preparing it for evolution.

name: N's Reshiram

attacks.name: Powerful Rage
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

flavorText: According to myth, if people ignore truth and let themselves become consumed by greed, Reshiram will arrive to burn their kingdoms down.

name: Dunsparce

attacks.name: Trading Places
attacks.text: Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: It creates mazes in dark locations. When spotted, it flees into the ground by digging with its tail.

name: Piloswine
flavorText: Covered by a shaggy coat, it is resistant to the cold. Its tusks of ice thicken when it snows.

name: Hop's Silicobra

attacks.name: Turf Maker
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Stadium card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: Silicobra's neck pouch, which can inflate and deflate like a balloon, gets more elastic each time Silicobra sheds its skin.

name: Hop's Sandaconda

attacks.name: Rumble
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Break Ground
attacks.text: This attack also does 20 damage to each of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It will expand its body as much as it can and then contract itself, blasting out sand with enough force to wash away a dump truck.

name: Klawf

attacks.name: Snipping Pincers
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. For each heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Klawf hangs upside-down from cliffs, waiting for prey. But Klawf can't remain in this position for long because its blood rushes to its head.

name: Pangoro

attacks.name: Torment
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't use that attack.

attacks.name: Power Tackle
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: Using its leaf, Pangoro can predict the moves of its opponents. It strikes with punches that can turn a dump truck into scrap with just one hit.

name: N's Klang

attacks.name: Spinning Gears
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokémon's rotation speed increases sharply.

name: Dudunsparce ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Tenacious Tail
attacks.text: This attack does 60 damage for each of your opponent's Pokémon ex in play.

attacks.name: Destructive Drill
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

name: Noivern

abilities.name: Tuning Echo
abilities.text: If you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent, ignore all Energy in the cost of Frightening Howl used by this Pokémon.

attacks.name: Frightening Howl
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Ultrasonic waves emitted by a Noivern can pulverize a large boulder. This Pokémon has a cruel disposition.

name: Noibat

attacks.name: Rapid Draw
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: This Pokémon emits ultrasonic waves from its large ears to search for fruit to eat. It mistakes Applin for its food.

name: Komala

attacks.name: Slumbering Smack
attacks.text: Both Active Pokémon are now Asleep. During your next turn, attacks used by this Pokémon do 100 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: Komala spends its entire life sleeping. It feeds on leaves that contain a potent poison only Komala can break down.

name: Hop's Rookidee

attacks.name: Intimidating Stare
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, attacks used by the Defending Pokémon do 20 less damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

flavorText: The females are fussier than the males. If another creature dirties a female Rookidee's wings, it'll peck the offender relentlessly in a burning rage.

name: Hop's Corvisquire
flavorText: This intelligent Pokémon will quickly learn how to use any tool it can hold in its beak or its talons.

name: Hop's Wooloo
flavorText: If its fleece grows too long, Wooloo won't be able to move. Cloth made with the wool of this Pokémon is surprisingly strong.

name: Hop's Dubwool

abilities.name: Defiant Horn
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.

flavorText: Its majestic horns are meant only to impress the opposite gender. They never see use in battle.

name: Hop's Cramorant

attacks.name: Fickle Spitting
attacks.text: If your opponent doesn't have exactly 3 or 4 Prize cards remaining, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: Cramorant instinctively swallow everything whole. They're at their most formidable when they're struggling to swallow overly large prey.

name: Brock's Scouting
rules: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Pokémon or 1 Evolution Pokémon, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Hop's Bag
rules: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Hop's Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Hop's Choice Band
rules: Attacks used by the Hop's Pokémon this card is attached to cost Colorless less and do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.

name: Iris's Fighting Spirit
rules: You can use this card only if you discard another card from your hand.  Draw cards until you have 6 cards in your hand.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Lillie's Pearl
rules: If the Lillie's Pokémon this card is attached to is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, that player takes 1 fewer Prize card.
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.

name: N's Castle
rules: N's Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Retreat Cost.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: N's PP Up
rules: Attach a Basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched N's Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Postwick
rules: Attacks used by Hop's Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) do 30 more damage to the opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

name: Redeemable Ticket
rules: Count your Prize cards, shuffle them, and put them on the bottom of your deck. Then, take that many cards from the top of your deck and put them face down as your Prize cards.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Ruffian
rules: Discard a Pokémon Tool and a Special Energy from 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

name: Super Potion
rules: Heal 60 damage from 1 of your Pokémon. If you healed any damage in this way, discard an Energy from that Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

name: Spiky Energy
rules: As long as this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides Colorless Energy.  If the Pokémon this card is attached to is in the Active Spot and is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokémon (even if this Pokémon is Knocked Out), put 2 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

name: Maractus

abilities.name: Exploding Needles
abilities.text: If this Pokémon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, put 6 damage counters on the Attacking Pokémon.

attacks.name: Corner
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

flavorText: Once each year, this Pokémon scatters its seeds. They're jam-packed with nutrients, making them a precious food source out in the desert.

name: Articuno

attacks.name: Frigid Fluttering
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Water Energy cards and attach them to this Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno is said to live in snowy mountains riddled with permafrost.

name: Wailord

attacks.name: Hydro Pump
attacks.text: This attack does 50 more damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon.

flavorText: Its immense size is the reason for its popularity. Wailord watching is a favorite sightseeing activity in various parts of the world.

name: Volcanion ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

abilities.name: Scalding Steam
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may make your opponent's Active Pokémon Burned.

attacks.name: Scorching Cyclone
attacks.text: Move an Energy from this Pokémon to 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

name: Shroomish
flavorText: It prefers damp places. By day it remains still in the forest shade. It releases toxic powder from its head.

name: Fomantis
flavorText: Fomantis hates having its naps interrupted. It fires off beams using energy it gathers by bathing in the sun.

name: Lurantis

attacks.name: Petal Blade Dance
attacks.text: Discard 2 Basic Grass Energy cards from your hand. If you can't discard 2 cards in this way, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: By masquerading as a bug Pokémon, it lowers the guard of actual bug Pokémon lured in by a scent of sweet flowers. Its sickles bring them down.

name: Dipplin

attacks.name: Energy Loop
attacks.text: Put an Energy attached to this Pokémon into your hand.

flavorText: Dipplin is two creatures in one Pokémon. Its evolution was triggered by a special apple grown only in one place.

name: Ethan's Cyndaquil

attacks.name: Ember
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It usually stays hunched over. If it is angry or surprised, it shoots flames out of its back.

name: Ethan's Quilava

abilities.name: Bonded by the Journey
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for an Ethan's Adventure card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: Before battle, it turns its back on its opponent to demonstrate how ferociously its fire blazes.

name: Team Rocket's Houndour
flavorText: It is smart enough to hunt in packs. It uses a variety of cries for communicating with others.

name: Heat Rotom

attacks.name: Singe
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

attacks.name: Gadget Show
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon Tool attached to all of your Pokémon.

flavorText: If the convection microwave oven is not working properly, then the Rotom inhabiting it will become lethargic.

name: Misty's Starmie

attacks.name: Abrupt Flash
attacks.text: If this Pokémon evolved from Misty's Staryu during this turn, this attack does 80 more damage.

flavorText: Starmie swims by spinning its body at high speed. As this Pokémon cruises through the ocean, it absorbs tiny plankton.

name: Cynthia's Feebas

attacks.name: Undulate
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: This tough Pokémon is perfectly fine even in dirty water. However, due to its ragged, shabby appearance, it isn't popular.

name: Floatzel

attacks.name: Whirlpool
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Aqua Slash
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: With its flotation sac inflated, it can carry people on its back. It deflates the sac before it dives.

name: Snover
flavorText: During cold seasons, it migrates to the mountain's lower reaches. It returns to the snow-covered summit in the spring.

name: Arrokuda

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: Arrokuda can swim quickly only in a straight line. The ones that become sluggish from overeating are the first to be targeted by flocks of Wattrel.

name: Electabuzz
flavorText: Its body constantly discharges electricity. Getting close to it will make your hair stand on end.

name: Team Rocket's Mareep

attacks.name: Procurement
attacks.text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: If static electricity builds in its body, its fleece doubles in volume. Touching it will shock you.

name: Team Rocket's Drowzee

attacks.name: Hypnotic Ray
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

flavorText: It remembers every dream it eats. It rarely eats the dreams of adults because children's are much tastier.

name: Steven's Claydol

attacks.name: Eerie Light
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

attacks.name: Clay Blast
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It appears to have been born from clay dolls made by ancient people. It uses telekinesis to float and move.

name: Team Rocket's Mimikyu

attacks.name: Gemstone Mimicry
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Tera Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

flavorText: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

name: Primeape

attacks.name: Drag Off
attacks.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. This attack does 30 damage to the new Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It becomes wildly furious if it even senses someone looking at it. It chases anyone that meets its glare.

name: Probopass

attacks.name: Mountain Drop
attacks.text: If a Stadium is in play, this attack does 70 more damage.

flavorText: It controls three units called Mini-Noses using magnetic force. With them, it can attack a foe from three directions.

name: Arven's Toedscool

attacks.name: Slight Intrusion
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: Toedscool lives in muggy forests. The flaps that fall from its body are chewy and very delicious.

name: Arven's Toedscruel

attacks.name: Pull
attacks.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.

attacks.name: Reckless Charge
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 30 damage to itself.

flavorText: These Pokémon gather into groups and form colonies deep within forests. They absolutely hate it when strangers approach.

name: Team Rocket's Arbok

abilities.name: Potent Glare
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, your opponent can't play any Pokémon that has an Ability from their hand, except for Team Rocket's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Spinning Tail
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: The pattern on its belly appears to be a frightening face. Weak foes will flee just at the sight of the pattern.

name: Team Rocket's Grimer

attacks.name: Corrosive Sludge
attacks.text: At the end of your opponent's next turn, discard the Defending Pokémon and all attached cards.

flavorText: Born from sludge, these Pokémon now gather in polluted places and increase the bacteria in their bodies.

name: Team Rocket's Muk

attacks.name: Gooped Up
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Hazardous Venom
attacks.text: This attack does 100 damage for each Special Condition affecting your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: It's thickly covered with a filthy, vile sludge. It is so toxic, even its footprints contain poison.

name: Marnie's Purrloin

attacks.name: Pointy Nails
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 40 more damage.

flavorText: Opponents that get drawn in by its adorable behavior come away with stinging scratches from its claws and stinging pride from its laughter.

name: Dwebble

attacks.name: Ascension
attacks.text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokémon and put it onto this Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It first tries to find a rock to live in, but if there are no suitable rocks to be found, Dwebble may move in to the ports of a Hippowdon.

name: Team Rocket's Blipbug

attacks.name: Searching Eyes
attacks.text: Look at 1 of your opponent's face-down Prize cards.

flavorText: Often found in gardens, this Pokémon has hairs on its body that it uses to assess its surroundings.

name: Growlithe
flavorText: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Ethan's Magcargo

abilities.name: Melt Away
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has no Energy attached, it has no Retreat Cost.

attacks.name: Lava Burst
attacks.text: Discard up to 5 Fire Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 70 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

flavorText: This Pokémon lives near the craters of volcanoes. It stores fire energy in its shell of cooled and hardened magma.

name: Buizel
flavorText: It spins its two tails like a screw to propel itself through water. The tails also slice clinging seaweed.

name: Barraskewda

attacks.name: Dive
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It spins its tail fins to leap from the water, then viciously bites down on Wingull flying close to the water's surface.

name: Wellspring Mask Ogerpon

attacks.name: Water Kagura
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Water Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Bubble Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: This form excels in both attack and defense. It ceaselessly unleashes moves like a spring gushes water.

name: Team Rocket's Ampharos

abilities.name: Darkest Impulse
abilities.text: Whenever your opponent plays a Pokémon from their hand to evolve 1 of their Pokémon, put 4 damage counters on that Pokémon. The effect of Darkest Impulse doesn't stack.

flavorText: The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.

name: Team Rocket's Hypno

attacks.name: Bench Manipulation
attacks.text: Your opponent flips a coin for each of their Benched Pokémon. This attack does 80 damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon for each tails. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

flavorText: When it locks eyes with an enemy, it will use a mix of psi moves, such as Hypnosis and Confusion.

name: Meditite

attacks.name: Steady Punch
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: It never skips its daily yoga training. It heightens its inner strength through meditation.

name: Team Rocket's Ekans

attacks.name: Drag Down
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It can freely detach its jaw to swallow large prey whole. It can become too heavy to move, however.

name: Team Rocket's Zubat

attacks.name: Poison Spray
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

flavorText: Zubat live in caves, down where the sun's light won't reach. In the morning, they gather together to keep each other warm as they sleep.

name: Team Rocket's Sneasel

attacks.name: Strike the Sleeper
attacks.text: This attack does 20 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon for each damage counter on that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: This cunning Pokémon hides under the cover of darkness, waiting to attack its prey.

name: Ethan's Pinsir

attacks.name: Rallying Horn
attacks.text: If any of your Ethan's Pokémon were Knocked Out by damage from an attack during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 100 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon clamps its pincers down on its prey and then either splits the prey in half or flings it away.

name: Breloom

attacks.name: Damage Rush
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 50 more damage for each heads.

attacks.name: Mega Drain
attacks.text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It scatters poisonous spores and throws powerful punches while its foe is hampered by inhaled spores.

name: Cynthia's Roselia
flavorText: It uses the different poisons in each hand separately when it attacks. The stronger its aroma, the healthier it is.

name: Mow Rotom

attacks.name: Trimming Mower
attacks.text: Discard a Stadium in play.

attacks.name: Gadget Show
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon Tool attached to all of your Pokémon.

flavorText: The lawn mower is one of the household appliances that led to the development of the Rotom Dex.

name: Applin

attacks.name: Mini Drain
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: It grows by eating the flesh of an apple. Applin uses its own body fluid to strengthen the apple's skin and prevent it from rotting.

name: Team Rocket's Tarountula

attacks.name: Take Down
attacks.text: This Pokémon also does 10 damage to itself.

flavorText: The ball of threads wrapped around its body is elastic enough to deflect the scythes of Scyther, this Pokémon's natural enemy.

name: Smoliv
flavorText: It protects itself from enemies by emitting oil from the fruit on its head. This oil is bitter and astringent enough to make someone flinch.

name: Teal Mask Ogerpon

attacks.name: Grass Kagura
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Grass Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Ogre's Hammer
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Ogre's Hammer.

flavorText: This Pokémon's type changes based on which mask it's wearing. It confounds its enemies with nimble movements and kicks.

name: Arcanine

attacks.name: Punishing Fang
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Darkness Pokémon, this attack does 100 more damage.

flavorText: An ancient picture scroll shows that people were captivated by its movement as it ran through prairies.

name: Ponyta

attacks.name: Double Headbutt
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

flavorText: If you've been accepted by Ponyta, its burning mane is mysteriously no longer hot to the touch.

name: Ethan's Slugma
flavorText: Its lava body can cool and chip away at times, but a magma bath will heal it right up.

name: Combusken

attacks.name: Double Kick
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It boosts its concentration by emitting harsh cries. Its kicks have outstanding destructive power.

name: Hearthflame Mask Ogerpon

attacks.name: Fire Kagura
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Fire Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: This form is the most aggressive, bombarding enemies with the intensity of flames blazing within a hearth.

name: Misty's Staryu

attacks.name: Bubble Beam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Fish Pokémon nibble at it, but Staryu isn't bothered. Its body regenerates quickly, even if part of it is completely torn off.

name: Cynthia's Milotic

attacks.name: Aqua Split
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Its lovely scales are described as rainbow colored. They change color depending on the viewing angle.

name: Huntail

abilities.name: Diver's Catch
abilities.text: When 1 of your Water Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, you may put all Basic Water Energy attached to that Pokémon into your hand instead of the discard pile.

flavorText: Deep seas are their habitat. According to tradition, when Huntail wash up onshore, something unfortunate will happen.

name: Gorebyss

attacks.name: Crescendo Wave
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Water Energy attached to this Pokémon. Before doing damage, you may attach any number of Basic Water Energy cards from your hand to this Pokémon.

flavorText: It sucks bodily fluids out of its prey. The leftover meat sinks to the seafloor, where it becomes food for other Pokémon.

name: Abomasnow

attacks.name: Frozen Wood
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has 2 or more Grass Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

flavorText: It lives a quiet life on mountains that are perpetually covered in snow. It hides itself by whipping up blizzards.

name: Wash Rotom

attacks.name: Manual Wash
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from each of your Pokémon.

attacks.name: Gadget Show
attacks.text: This attack does 30 damage for each Pokémon Tool attached to all of your Pokémon.

flavorText: This Rotom has entered a washing machine. It nods with satisfaction after it floods the surrounding area.

name: Zeraora

attacks.name: Thunder Raid
attacks.text: Discard all Energy from this Pokémon, and this attack does 210 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon ex. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: Electricity sparks from the pads on its limbs. Wherever Zeraora runs, lightning flashes and thunder echoes.

name: Steven's Baltoy

attacks.name: Summoning Sign
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 Basic Steven's Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: It was discovered in ancient ruins. While moving, it constantly spins. It stands on one foot even when asleep.

name: Annihilape

abilities.name: Lose Cool
abilities.text: If this Pokémon has 2 or more damage counters on it, attacks used by this Pokémon do 120 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

attacks.name: Impact Blow
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't use Impact Blow.

flavorText: When its anger rose beyond a critical point, this Pokémon gained power that is unfettered by the limits of its physical body.

name: Ethan's Sudowoodo

attacks.name: Impound
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat.

attacks.name: Try to Imitate
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokémon's attacks and use it as this attack.

flavorText: Although it always pretends to be a tree, its composition appears more similar to rock than to vegetation.

name: Team Rocket's Tyranitar

abilities.name: Sand Stream
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, put 2 damage counters on each of your opponent's Basic Pokémon.

attacks.name: Demolition Tackle
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Extremely strong, it can change the landscape. It is so insolent that it doesn't care about others.

name: Cynthia's Gible

attacks.name: Rock Hurl
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Resistance.

flavorText: It skulks in caves, and when prey or an enemy passes by, it leaps out and chomps them. The force of its attack sometimes chips its teeth.

name: Cynthia's Gabite

abilities.name: Champion's Call
abilities.text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for a Cynthia's Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: In rare cases, it molts and sheds its scales. Medicine containing its scales as an ingredient will make a weary body feel invigorated.

name: Mudbray

attacks.name: Running Charge
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 40 damage for each heads.

flavorText: This Pokémon covers itself in mud that it has regurgitated. The mud won't dry out even if it's exposed to the sun for a long time.

name: Cornerstone Mask Ogerpon

attacks.name: Rock Kagura
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Basic Fighting Energy card and attach it to 1 of your Pokémon. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Mountain Ramming
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

flavorText: This form has excellent defenses, absorbing impacts solidly like the cornerstones that support houses.

name: Team Rocket's Nidoran♀

attacks.name: Surprise Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It uses its hard incisor teeth to crush and eat berries. The tip of a female Nidoran's horn is a bit more rounded than the tip of a male's horn.

name: Team Rocket's Nidorina

attacks.name: Dark Awakening
attacks.text: Choose up to 2 of your Darkness Pokémon. For each of those Pokémon, search your deck for a card that evolves from that Pokémon and put it onto that Pokémon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

flavorText: If the group is threatened, these Pokémon will band together to assault enemies with a chorus of ultrasonic waves.

name: Team Rocket's Nidoqueen

attacks.name: Love Impact
attacks.text: If a Pokémon that has "Nidoking" in its name is on your Bench, this attack does 120 more damage.

flavorText: It pacifies offspring by placing them in the gaps between the spines on its back. The spines will never secrete poison while young are present.

name: Team Rocket's Nidoran♂
flavorText: Small but brave, this Pokémon will hold its ground and even risk its life in battle to protect the female it's friendly with.

name: Team Rocket's Nidorino

attacks.name: Horn Rend
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: It's nervous and quick to act aggressively. The potency of its poison increases along with the level of adrenaline present in its body.

name: Team Rocket's Golbat

abilities.name: Sneaky Bite
abilities.text: When you play this Pokémon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokémon during your turn, you may put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Confuse Ray
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused.

flavorText: Its feet are tiny, but this Pokémon walks skillfully. It sneaks up on sleeping prey before sinking in its fangs and slurping up blood.

name: Cynthia's Spiritomb

attacks.name: Raging Curse
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage for each damage counter on all of your Benched Cynthia's Pokémon. This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness.

flavorText: Its constant mischief and misdeeds resulted in it being bound to an Odd Keystone by a mysterious spell.

name: Pineco
flavorText: It likes to make its shell thicker by adding layers of tree bark. The additional weight doesn't bother it.

name: Dolliv

attacks.name: Nutrients
attacks.text: Heal 40 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.

flavorText: Dolliv shares its tasty, fresh-scented oil with others. This species has coexisted with humans since times long gone.

name: Torchic

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: Torchic feels toasty warm if you hug it. It has a flame sac inside its belly, and the flames burn continuously as long as Torchic has life in it.

name: Misty's Magikarp

abilities.name: So Submerged
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks from your opponent's Pokémon done to this Pokémon.

flavorText: An underpowered, pathetic Pokémon. It may jump high on rare occasions but never more than seven feet.

name: Misty's Gyarados

attacks.name: Splashing Panic
attacks.text: Discard the top 7 cards of your deck, and this attack does 70 damage for each Misty's Pokémon that you discarded in this way.

flavorText: Once it appears, it goes on a rampage. It remains enraged until it demolishes everything around it.

name: Team Rocket's Articuno

abilities.name: Repelling Veil
abilities.text: Prevent all effects of attacks used by your opponent's Pokémon done to your Basic Team Rocket's Pokémon. (Existing effects are not removed. Damage is not an effect.)

attacks.name: Dark Frost
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Team Rocket's Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon can control ice at will. Articuno is said to live in snowy mountains riddled with permafrost.

name: Cetoddle
flavorText: This species left the ocean and began living on land a very long time ago. It seems to be closely related to Wailmer.

name: Team Rocket's Zapdos

attacks.name: Jamming Wing
attacks.text: You may move an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon to 1 of their Benched Pokémon.

attacks.name: Wicked Thunder
attacks.text: If this Pokémon has any Team Rocket's Energy attached, this attack does 60 more damage.

flavorText: Zapdos is a legendary bird Pokémon. It's said that when Zapdos rubs its feathers together, lightning will fall immediately after.

name: Ethan's Pichu

attacks.name: Zapping Draw
attacks.text: Draw a card.

flavorText: It is unskilled at storing electric power. Any kind of shock causes it to discharge energy spontaneously.

name: Team Rocket's Flaaffy

attacks.name: Thunder Shock
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: As a result of storing too much electricity, it developed patches where even downy wool won't grow.

name: Manectric

attacks.name: Flash Impact
attacks.text: This attack also does 40 damage to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

flavorText: It rarely appears before people. It is said to nest where lightning has fallen.

name: Team Rocket's Chingling

attacks.name: Chiming Commotion
attacks.text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

flavorText: There is an orb inside its mouth. When it hops, the orb bounces all over and makes a ringing sound.

name: Steven's Carbink

abilities.name: Stone Palace
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is on your Bench, all of your Steven's Pokémon take 30 less damage from attacks from your opponent's Pokémon (after applying Weakness and Resistance). The effect of Stone Palace doesn't stack.

flavorText: It has slept underground for hundreds of millions of years since its birth. It's occasionally found during the excavation of caves.

name: Team Rocket's Dottler

attacks.name: Disruptive Radar
attacks.text: Look at the top 5 cards of your opponent's deck and put them back in any order.

flavorText: As it grows inside its shell, it uses its psychic abilities to monitor the outside world and prepare for evolution.

name: Mankey

attacks.name: Wild Kick
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

flavorText: It lives in groups in the treetops. If it loses sight of its group, it becomes infuriated by its loneliness.

name: Team Rocket's Larvitar

attacks.name: Mountain Munch
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

flavorText: Born deep underground, this Pokémon becomes a pupa after eating enough dirt to make a mountain.

name: Caterpie
flavorText: Its short feet are tipped with suction pads that enable it to tirelessly climb slopes and walls.

name: Metapod

attacks.name: Harden
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks if that damage is 60 or less.

flavorText: Even though it is encased in a sturdy shell, the body inside is tender. It can't withstand a harsh attack.

name: Karrablast

attacks.name: Push Down
attacks.text: Switch out your opponent's Active Pokémon to the Bench. (Your opponent chooses the new Active Pokémon.)

flavorText: It spits a liquid from its mouth to melt through Shelmet's shell. Karrablast doesn't eat the shell— it eats only the contents.

name: Paras

attacks.name: Leech Life
attacks.text: Heal from this Pokémon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokémon.

flavorText: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

name: Butterfree

attacks.name: Scale Hurricane
attacks.text: Flip 4 coins. This attack does 60 damage for each heads. If at least 2 of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It collects honey every day. It rubs honey onto the hairs on its legs to carry it back to its nest.

name: Parasect

attacks.name: Spore
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

attacks.name: Scissor Swing
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

flavorText: The larger the mushroom on its back grows, the stronger the mushroom spores it scatters.

name: Shelmet

attacks.name: Shell Smack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks.

flavorText: It has a strange physiology that responds to electricity. When together with Karrablast, Shelmet evolves for some reason.

name: Sprigatito

attacks.name: Tons of Treading
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage for each heads.

flavorText: Its fluffy fur is similar in composition to plants. This Pokémon frequently washes its face to keep it from drying out.

name: Floragato

attacks.name: Magical Leaf
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage, and heal 30 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: Floragato deftly wields the vine hidden beneath its long fur, slamming the hard flower bud against its opponents.

name: Accelgor

attacks.name: Poisonous Ploy
attacks.text: Your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Confused and Poisoned. Switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

flavorText: Discarding its shell made it nimble. To keep itself from dehydrating, it wraps its body in bands of membrane.

name: Meowscarada

abilities.name: Showtime
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokémon.

attacks.name: Rising Bloom
attacks.text: If your opponent's Active Pokémon is a Pokémon ex, this attack does 90 more damage.

flavorText: This Pokémon uses the reflective fur lining its cape to camouflage the stem of its flower, creating the illusion that the flower is floating.

name: Magmar

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: Found near the mouth of a volcano. This fire-breather's body temperature is nearly 2,200 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: Magmortar

abilities.name: Magma Surge
abilities.text: During Pokémon Checkup, put 3 more damage counters on your opponent's Burned Pokémon.

attacks.name: Searing Flame
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Burned.

flavorText: When shooting 3,600 degree Fahrenheit fireballs from its arms, its body takes on a whitish hue from the intense heat.

name: N's Darumaka
flavorText: This popular symbol of good fortune will never fall over in its sleep, no matter how it's pushed or pulled.

name: Remoraid

attacks.name: Flail
attacks.text: This attack does 10 damage for each damage counter on this Pokémon.

flavorText: Using its dorsal fin as a suction pad, it clings to a Mantine's underside to scavenge for leftovers.

name: Octillery

attacks.name: Aqua Wash
attacks.text: You may put an Energy attached to your opponent's Active Pokémon into their hand.

attacks.name: Octo Beatdown
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 90 damage for each heads.

flavorText: It traps enemies with its suction-cupped tentacles, then smashes them with its rock-hard head.

name: Lombre

attacks.name: Aqua Slash
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

flavorText: Old folklore in Kitakami tells of a mischievous child who was reborn as a Pokémon.

name: Ludicolo

abilities.name: Vibrant Dance
abilities.text: All of your Pokémon in play get +40 HP. The effect of Vibrant Dance doesn't stack.

flavorText: There are structures throughout its whole body that produce energy when hit by sound waves with a cheerful rhythm.

name: Lotad
flavorText: The leaf on its head is naturally dirt repellent and will stay clean even after transporting Pokémon that are covered in mud.

name: Wailmer
flavorText: When it sucks in a large volume of seawater, it becomes like a big, bouncy ball. It eats a ton of food daily.

name: Iono's Voltorb

attacks.name: Voltaic Chain
attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Lightning Energy attached to all of your Iono's Pokémon.

flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

name: Iono's Electrode

attacks.name: Thump-Thump Boom
attacks.text: This Pokémon does 100 damage to itself. Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is Knocked Out.

flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

name: N's Joltik

attacks.name: Zapping Short
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon. If you discarded a Pokémon Tool in this way, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: Since it can't generate its own electricity, it sticks onto large-bodied Pokémon and absorbs static electricity.

name: Iono's Wattrel

attacks.name: Quick Attack
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

flavorText: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.

name: Mr. Mime

attacks.name: Mimic
attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw a card for each card in your opponent's hand.

attacks.name: Psy Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

flavorText: It's known for its top-notch pantomime skills. It protects itself from all sorts of attacks by emitting auras from its fingers to create walls.

name: Beldum
flavorText: The magnetic force generated by its body repels the ground's natural magnetism, letting it float.

name: Iono's Tadbulb
flavorText: Tadbulb shakes its tail to generate electricity. If it senses danger, it will make its head blink on and off to alert its allies.

name: Shuppet
flavorText: It loves to feed on feelings like envy and malice. Its upright horn catches the emotions of people.

name: Banette

attacks.name: Cursed Words
attacks.text: Your opponent chooses 3 cards from their hand and shuffles those cards into their deck.

flavorText: This Pokémon developed from an abandoned doll that amassed a grudge. It is seen in dark alleys.

name: Metang
flavorText: It is formed by two Beldum joining together. Its two brains are linked, amplifying its psychic power.

name: Lillie's Cutiefly

attacks.name: Hold Still
attacks.text: Heal 10 damage from this Pokémon.

flavorText: When it senses the auras of people or Pokémon who are having fun, it will draw close and give them a painful poke with its long proboscis.

name: Lillie's Comfey

attacks.name: Inviting Flowers
attacks.text: You may search your deck for any number of Basic Lillie's Pokémon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

attacks.name: Fade Out
attacks.text: Put this Pokémon and all attached cards into your hand.

flavorText: It uses its vine to pick flowers. The flowers that Comfey attaches to itself develop healing properties.
